.SH "NAME"
skb_gso_network_seglen \- Return length of individual segments of a gso packet
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'unsigned\ int\ skb_gso_network_seglen('u
.BI "unsigned int skb_gso_network_seglen(const\ struct\ sk_buff\ *\ " "skb" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIskb\fR
.RS 4
GSO skb
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
skb_gso_network_seglen is used to determine the real size of the individual segments, including Layer3 (IP, IPv6) and L4 headers (TCP/UDP)\&.
.PP
The MAC/L2 header is not accounted for\&.
